"Malcolm" == Malcolm Ross Kinsella Ryan <malcolmr@cse.unsw.edu.au> writes:

Malcolm> BTW: Any comments on the layout? Gen Chaos' numbered clauses
Malcolm> seemed appropriate.

If you want to be consistent with what I am using, please follow the
following standards:

For text not set out with an indexed subdivision, indent six spaces on
the left margin.  Otherwise the indent is ten spaces plus two spaces
for each sublevel.  The indexing tag hangs into the margin.  Right
margin is always at column 70.

All indexing tags are enclosed in parenthesis.  Do not put two tags on
the same line; if you want a division with no non-subdivided text,
leave the line after the tag blank.

The first level of tags is lowercase letters; use "aa", "bb", etc
after "z".  The second level is digits.  The third level is uppercase
letters.  Fourth and subsequent levels repeat this pattern: hence,
(a)(1)(A)(a)(1).  (I hope that we never need more than three levels.)
I don't use roman numerals because they take up a lot of space.

Blank lines between paragraphs only for first-level and unindexed
paragraphs.  (This is more open to reasonable variation.)

I have a Perl script that takes a marked-up format and prettifies it,
if anyone is interested.

