Steve wrote:

>I remind Registrar Andre he is required to conduct an Election for the
>Office of Treasuror.

>Which raises an interesting question. Assume that my Proposal to make
>the Xmas/New Year period a Holiday is adopted, and assume (which seems
>reasonable), that the Holiday will then commence (de facto) at the time
>the Proposal is adopted. Question: will this affect Players' ability to
>nominate in this Election (assuming further that Andre has called for
>nominations by then)?

>R1769 (Holidays) states that:

>     If some Rule requires that an action be done prior to a given time,
>     and that given time falls during a Holiday, or within the
>     twenty-four-hour period immediately following that Holiday, then
>     that action need not be done until twenty-four hours after that
>     Holiday ends.

>I can see arguments for both sides. On the one hand, no-one is required
>to nominate in an Election. On the other hand, if one wants to nominate
>in an Election, one is required to do so before the end of the
>Nominating Period.

>Opinions?

Here is a thought that I present only, maybe, half-seriously.  If the end of a
Nominating Period falls within a Holiday, then it is possible to nominate
for an Office by doing it *exacly* 24 hours after the end of the Holiday. 8)

OTOH, the more I read the Rule, it seems to me to grant an automatic
extension of the Nominating Period.  Although the Rules do not
require you to nominate, if you want to, they *do* require you to do it
before the end of the NP.

--Crito

